HPV - p16 & SYNGR3 + 2-positive samples

Best p16 and SYNGR3

Alisha Coffey

p16 sheet has 2 columns labeled MED+HIGH nuc_Stroma 
all <- read_xlsx("~/Desktop/HPV_p16_Syngr3/NewAnalysisResults/AUC_all_variables/20210330_syngr3 v p16.xlsx",sheet=1)
syngr3 <- all[,c(2,4,which(grepl("syngr3",colnames(all),ignore.case = T)==T))]
p16 <- all[,c(2,which(grepl("p16",colnames(all),ignore.case = T)==T))]


# identical(p16$Core_ID,syngr3$Core_ID...1)
# identical(p16$`HPV status (ISH)`,syngr3$`HPV status (ISH)`)

measures <- merge(syngr3,p16,by.x=1,by.y=1)
measures$ddPCR.status[which(measures$ddPCR.status=="NA")] <- "HPV-pos"

for(i in 1:nrow(measures)){
    for(j in 1:ncol(measures)){
        if(measures[i,j]=="NA"){
            measures[i,j] <- NA
        }
    }
}

By Core

colnames(measures) <- tolower(colnames(measures))
measures_orig <- measures
status <- as.factor(measures$ddpcr.status)

# measures <- measures[,-2]

comparisons <- list(c("med\\.high", "positive"), c("whole","tumor","stroma"))

Compute the p-value of binary test at core level using wilcox (Mann-Whitney test)

ttest.p.core <- c()
for(i in 3:ncol(measures)){
        ttest.p.core <- rbind(ttest.p.core,data.frame(colnames(measures)[i], wilcox.test(as.numeric(measures[,i]) ~ status)$p.value))
}
colnames(ttest.p.core) <- c("Measurement", "P-Value")



### multiple test correction
ttest.p.core$FDR<- p.adjust(ttest.p.core$`P-Value`, method='fdr', n = length(ttest.p.core$`P-Value`))
ttest.p.core$AUC <- sapply(ttest.p.core$Measurement,function(x){roc(predictor = as.numeric(measures[,x]),response = status == "HPV-pos")$auc[1]})

# write.table(ttest.p.core, file="~/Desktop/HPV_p16_Syngr3/NewAnalysisResults/PValues_MannWhitTest_ByCore.tsv",sep = "\t",quote = F,row.names = F)

ttest.p.core.p16 <- ttest.p.core[grepl("p16",ttest.p.core$Measurement)==TRUE,]
ttest.p.core.p16 <- ttest.p.core.p16[order(ttest.p.core.p16$AUC,decreasing = T),]
ttest.p.core.syngr3 <- ttest.p.core[grepl("p16",ttest.p.core$Measurement)==FALSE,]
ttest.p.core.syngr3 <- ttest.p.core.syngr3[order(ttest.p.core.syngr3$AUC,decreasing = T),]



kable(ttest.p.core.p16) %>% kable_styling()

best p16 and best SYNGR3

medhigh_syngr3_roc <- roc(predictor = as.numeric(measures[,"syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor"]),response = status == "HPV-pos")
plot.roc(medhigh_syngr3_roc ,main = "Med+High- SYNGR3 stroma and p16 cyto tumor",add = FALSE, cex.main=0.8, print.auc=TRUE ,print.auc.x=0.0,print.auc.y= 0.4 ,col = "blue")

medhigh_p16_roc <- roc(predictor = as.numeric(measures[,"p16_med.high.cyto_tumor"]),response = status == "HPV-pos")
plot.roc(medhigh_p16_roc ,add = TRUE, cex.main=0.8, print.auc=TRUE ,print.auc.x=0.0,print.auc.y= 0.35 ,col = "red")

tog <- as.numeric(measures[,"p16_med.high.cyto_tumor"]) + as.numeric(measures[,"syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor"])
medhigh_tog_roc <- roc(predictor = as.numeric(tog),response = status == "HPV-pos")
plot.roc(medhigh_tog_roc, add = TRUE, cex.main=0.8, print.auc=TRUE ,print.auc.x=0.0,print.auc.y= 0.3 ,col = "goldenrod3")

legend("bottomright",legend =c("syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor","p16_med.high.cyto_tumor", "both together"),col=c("blue","red","goldenrod3"),lty=c(rep(1,3),2,2,1),bty='n',cex=0.8)

tog <- as.data.frame(tog)

ggplot(tog, aes(x = status, y = tog)) + 
                  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA) + geom_jitter( shape = 3, color = "blue") + 
                  ylab("") + xlab("HPV Status") +
                  annotate("text",label=paste("p =",round(wilcox.test(tog$tog ~ status)$p.value,10)),x=1.5,y=max(tog,na.rm=T)) +
                  theme_bw() + ggtitle("p16_med.high.cyto_tumor + syngr3_..positive cells_tumor") +
                  theme(plot.title = element_text(color = "black", hjust = 0.5), axis.text = element_text(color="black",size = 12))

Precision vs recall

library(PRROC)
# making status numeric
status01 <- as.character(status)
status01[status01 == "HPV-neg"] <- 0
status01[status01 == "HPV-pos"] <- 1
status01 <- as.numeric(status01)


# removing NAs because NAs cause error messages
x <- as.numeric(measures$p16_med.high.cyto_tumor[which(is.na(measures$p16_med.high.cyto_tumor)==FALSE)])
st <- status01[which(is.na(measures$p16_med.high.cyto_tumor)==FALSE)]

p16_pr <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = x, weights.class0 = st, curve = TRUE)


x <- as.numeric(measures$syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor)
st <- status01[which(is.na(measures$syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor)==FALSE)]
syn_pr <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = x,weights.class0 = st, curve = TRUE)


x <- tog$tog[which(is.na(tog$tog)==FALSE)]
st <- status01[which(is.na(tog$tog)==FALSE)]
tog_pr <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = x,weights.class0 = st, curve = TRUE)
plot(p16_pr,color="red",main = "Precision-Recall Curve\nsyngr3_..positive.cells_tumor  +  p16_med.high.cyto_tumor",auc.main=FALSE)
plot(syn_pr,color="blue", add=TRUE,auc.main=FALSE)
plot(tog_pr,color="goldenrod3",add=TRUE,auc.main=FALSE)
legend(x=0.05,y=0.55,legend =c("syngr3_..positive.cells_tumor","p16_med.high.cyto_tumor", "both together"),col=c("blue","red","goldenrod3"),lty=c(rep(1,3),2,2,1),bty='n',cex=0.8)
text(x=0.15, y=0.25, labels = paste("AUC:",round(syn_pr$auc.integral,3)),col="blue")
text(x=0.15, y=0.20, labels = paste("AUC:",round(p16_pr$auc.integral,3)),col="red")
text(x=0.15, y=0.15, labels = paste("AUC:",round(tog_pr$auc.integral,3)),col="goldenrod3")
